Metadata came first, before any search existed. Every note got structured properties from the start: type, related project, status. This was human indexing, designed for my own eyes.

In hindsight, the filing system I'd built for human navigation turned out to be a powerful structured query layer. Structural queries ("all meetings for this project in the last month") can be answered without the AI touching a single file.

Metadata shows every meeting for a project but can't tell me which meetings keep circling back to the same unresolved question. [[semantic-search|Semantic search]] clusters them by theme.
